Nigerian singer, Timi Dakolo stamped his voice in the hearts of several Nigerians, today the 28th of November in Abuja. The RnB singer did this by performing at not one, not two or even four, but eight wedding receptions for free. <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Timi-Dakolo-performs-at-wedding-foc-331x420.png" alt="Timi Dakolo Performs at wedding free"/> Timi Dakolo with the first of the eight couples he performed for This happened after he made an Instagram post where he asked couples to drop addresses to their wedding receptions. The post read “I am feeling good today. Dear Abuja people, who is marrying today? Drop the address and let me have the privilege of singing for you guys and leave a lasting memory.” RELATED POST: Banky W, 2Baba, Timi Dakolo, Waje, Seun Kuti and others call for a better Nigeria in 'Talk And Do' <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Timi-Dakolo-wedding-request-419x420.png" alt="Timi Dakolo Abuja weddings"/> Timi Dakolo's request to perform at weddings That request then grew into Timi Dakolo making an appearance at 8 wedding receptions where he performed his romantic hits such as ‘Iyawo Mi’, ‘The Vow’ and ‘Medicine’ to elated couples and their guests. Guys, how would you feel if Timi Dakolo showed up at your wedding and performed for free? View this post on Instagram A post shared by Timi dakolo (@timidakolo) The post Beautiful! Watch Timi Dakolo Perform at 8 Weddings for Free In Abuja appeared first on Most Trusted Voice in Music & Afrobeats from Nigeria & Africa | Notjustok. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.